Parliament, Wednesday, 31 October 2018 – The Joint Constitutional Review Committee will tomorrow, 01 November 2018, consider the draft report on a possible review of section 25 of the Constitution. Details are as follows: 
	Date: Thursday, 01 November 2018
	Time: 10:00
	Venue: Committee Room V475, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building. ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CO-CHAIRPERSON OF THE JOINT CONSTITUTIONAL REVIEW COMMITTEE, MR LEWIS NZIMANDE AND ACTING CO-CHAIRPERSON, MR STANFORD MAILA. For media enquiries or interviews, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Rajaa Azzakani (Ms)
	Tel: 021 403 8437
	Cell: 081 703 9542
	E-mail: razzakani@parliament.gov.za Democracy is not an event that occurred in 1994. It is a process to which all of us can contribute by making our voices heard in Parliament, in the provincial legislatures and in broader society.Read more